.TH GETTID 2CCC
.SH NAME
gettid \- return the task id of the currently running task
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tid = gettid()
.br
.B int tid;
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Gettid
returns the task id of the currently executing task.
It is necessary to be able to identify one's self in order to
perform some operations (e.g., change one's scheduling priority).
